<section class="section" id="how-it-works">
  <div class="section-heading">
    <p class="eyebrow">What ShipFlow Is</p>
    <h2>The operating model around AI-generated work.</h2>
    <p>
      AI can produce code faster than your old process can safely absorb it.
      ShipFlow connects the agent workflow, the decision contracts, and the
      server lifecycle so the output has somewhere disciplined to land.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="split-grid">
    <article class="panel">
      <h3>Delivery discipline for agents</h3>
      <ul class="check-list">
        <li>route a fresh agent to the right context fast</li>
        <li>shape non-trivial work before coding starts</li>
        <li>verify against contracts instead of hope</li>
        <li>keep business, product, and docs traceable</li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <article class="panel">
      <h3>Server control for real shipping</h3>
      <ul class="check-list">
        <li>run isolated environments with Flox</li>
        <li>manage processes and lifecycle with PM2</li>
        <li>publish through Caddy and DuckDNS</li>
        <li>use tunnels, checks, and runtime operations without duct tape</li>
      </ul>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>
